17
00:00:12,297 --> 00:00:12,414
http://hiqve.com/

18
00:00:12,415 --> 00:00:15,415
http://hiqve.com/

19
00:00:18,439 --> 00:00:20,358
<i>Secret transmission
intercepted!</i>

20
00:00:21,108 --> 00:00:24,278
<i>The Jedi Council has intercepted
an encoded transmission</i>

21
00:00:24,362 --> 00:00:25,446
<i>of General Grievous.</i>

22
00:00:25,530 --> 00:00:27,698
<i>However, Republic intelligence officers</i>

23
00:00:27,782 --> 00:00:29,784
<i>have failed to crack
the new encryption code</i>

24
00:00:29,825 --> 00:00:31,327
<i>being used by the droids.</i>

25
00:00:31,786 --> 00:00:36,082
<i>Fears escalate that the Separatists
are about the mount a major offensive.</i>

26
00:00:36,123 --> 00:00:39,669
<i>Having located the source of
the transmission deep in Separatist space,</i>

27
00:00:39,794 --> 00:00:43,923
<i>the Jedi plan a counter-strike
to capture an enemy decoding chip</i>

28
00:00:44,131 --> 00:00:46,259
<i>which will allow them
to understand the transmission</i>

29
00:00:46,759 --> 00:00:49,095
<i>and thwart the Separatist plot.</i>

30
00:00:52,848 --> 00:00:55,935
Time is not on our side,
so I'll make this short.

31
00:00:56,102 --> 00:00:59,188
You droids have been chosen
for a very important mission.

32
00:01:01,315 --> 00:01:04,485
There's an encryption module
on board this Separatist dreadnought.

33
00:01:04,610 --> 00:01:08,447
This device is scrambling
all Separatist communication in the region.

34
00:01:08,489 --> 00:01:11,534
We believe you five
can get behind enemy lines,

35
00:01:11,659 --> 00:01:14,620
infiltrate the vault
without drawing attention to yourselves,

36
00:01:14,662 --> 00:01:17,164
and steal that encryption module.

37
00:01:24,088 --> 00:01:26,173
WAC-47 reporting for duty!

38
00:01:26,674 --> 00:01:28,843
Sorry I am late, I thought the message said

39
00:01:28,968 --> 00:01:32,680
to meet in the Jedi Storeroom,
whatever that is.

40
00:01:33,014 --> 00:01:34,849
So? Did I miss anything?

41
00:01:35,182 --> 00:01:37,184
Fall in line, soldier.

42
00:01:45,943 --> 00:01:49,280
So I hear we're gonna be
taking out Separatists!

43
00:01:51,449 --> 00:01:55,494
I will be honest,
some of you may not make it back.

44
00:01:55,703 --> 00:01:57,330
What? Why is he looking at me?

45
00:01:57,788 --> 00:01:58,831
Uh...

46
00:01:58,873 --> 00:02:00,708
Were you just looking at me?

47
00:02:03,169 --> 00:02:04,545
I was just kidding.

48
00:02:04,670 --> 00:02:06,088
But I have faith in your abilities.

49
00:02:06,797 --> 00:02:09,091
You are not ordinary droids.

50
00:02:09,300 --> 00:02:11,260
You've worked with the Jedi before.

51
00:02:11,636 --> 00:02:14,305
You are our secret weapons.

52
00:02:14,972 --> 00:02:17,516
Now, let me turn you over
to your mission leader.

53
00:02:17,933 --> 00:02:21,187
The Colonel is one of our top minds
at Strategic Command.

54
00:02:21,270 --> 00:02:24,273
He's been with the Republic
since the Battle of Geonosis.

55
00:02:24,357 --> 00:02:26,359
Colonel Meebur Gascon.

56
00:02:36,118 --> 00:02:39,330
Thank you, Master Windu.
I'll take it from here.

57
00:02:40,039 --> 00:02:42,083
May the Force be with you.

58
00:02:52,176 --> 00:02:53,386
Attention!

59
00:02:57,348 --> 00:03:01,811
Now, I'm only going to say this once,
so turn up your audio inputs.

60
00:03:04,146 --> 00:03:07,191
Once we're inside the cruiser,
we make our way to C deck.

61
00:03:07,274 --> 00:03:10,528
That's where their
communication center is housed.

62
00:03:10,695 --> 00:03:12,988
We bypass security here and here,

63
00:03:13,072 --> 00:03:14,949
divert the super battle droids here,

64
00:03:15,032 --> 00:03:17,284
then we break the vault code,
beat the swarm mines,

65
00:03:17,368 --> 00:03:19,787
steal the encryption module,
and return home in time

66
00:03:19,870 --> 00:03:22,373
for my promotion ceremony
to Brigadier General.

67
00:03:22,623 --> 00:03:24,041
Are we clear?

68
00:03:29,672 --> 00:03:31,132
Uh, uh...

69
00:03:31,215 --> 00:03:34,593
Good ! That's what I like. No questions.

70
00:03:35,052 --> 00:03:36,137
Oh.

71
00:03:36,387 --> 00:03:38,556
D Squad, fall in line!

72
00:03:49,650 --> 00:03:51,736
The line starts behind me, mech.

73
00:04:15,009 --> 00:04:17,678
Over here, you mechs! Front and center!

74
00:04:18,512 --> 00:04:21,015
This is Dr. Gubacher. He is...

75
00:04:21,098 --> 00:04:22,850
Corporal?

76
00:04:23,434 --> 00:04:24,602
Colonel.

77
00:04:25,019 --> 00:04:28,063
Right. Well, I just want
to set the record straight.

78
00:04:28,189 --> 00:04:29,523
I am not a mech.

79
00:04:29,774 --> 00:04:33,611
You called us all mechs back there.
But, as you can see, I am a WAC.

80
00:04:34,111 --> 00:04:35,863
Granted, my master's not a Jedi,

81
00:04:35,946 --> 00:04:38,282
but I am a different class of droid.

82
00:04:38,616 --> 00:04:41,076
Better engineering.

83
00:04:42,953 --> 00:04:47,458
As I was saying
before I was rudely interrupted,

84
00:04:47,541 --> 00:04:50,377
Dr. Gubacher is going to equip each of you

85
00:04:50,461 --> 00:04:54,381
with a tactical upgrade
specially designed for this mission.

86
00:04:54,465 --> 00:04:57,218
All right, enough with the chatter!

87
00:04:57,301 --> 00:04:59,386
Let's get this show on the road.

88
00:04:59,804 --> 00:05:04,225
Cyclops! You're not needed here.
Go prepare our shuttle for launch!

89
00:05:14,985 --> 00:05:19,114
R2-D2, these advanced rocket boosters

90
00:05:19,240 --> 00:05:22,743
should give you better aerial mobility,

91
00:05:22,868 --> 00:05:25,371
and for longer periods of time.

92
00:05:25,579 --> 00:05:27,206
Oh, but be advised,

93
00:05:27,248 --> 00:05:30,960
the navigation controls are finely tuned.

94
00:05:31,710 --> 00:05:36,757
QT-KT, this coil
is a remote-controlled magnet.

95
00:05:37,091 --> 00:05:41,387
It can attract any metal object
in a seven-meter radius.

96
00:05:42,304 --> 00:05:46,600
But when dealing with mines,
you'll want to take care.

97
00:05:47,142 --> 00:05:50,563
The magnetic force is extremely powerful.

98
00:05:51,230 --> 00:05:54,066
U9-C4, this laser-cutter

99
00:05:54,108 --> 00:05:58,320
will slice through
most materials you encounter.

100
00:05:58,737 --> 00:06:01,448
But make sure you're in a locked position.

101
00:06:03,951 --> 00:06:07,580
The recoil packs quite a wallop.

102
00:06:13,085 --> 00:06:14,420
No, no, no, no, no.

103
00:06:14,461 --> 00:06:18,340
M5-BZ, we are not putting
anything inside you,

104
00:06:19,258 --> 00:06:21,135
we're taking something out.

105
00:06:21,260 --> 00:06:22,970
Your memory banks.

106
00:06:24,680 --> 00:06:29,435
I'll be making the extraction myself
in the Salvage Room.

107
00:06:33,272 --> 00:06:37,693
I am sorry, but we need to make room
for the Colonel's command center.

108
00:06:37,943 --> 00:06:41,947
No need to baby him. He's just a droid.

109
00:06:42,448 --> 00:06:46,660
Fortunately, he won't remember
any of this.

110
00:07:02,343 --> 00:07:04,303
What do you want, Beezee?

111
00:07:04,345 --> 00:07:06,180
It's me, you moron.

112
00:07:06,680 --> 00:07:08,390
What are you doing in there, Corporal?

113
00:07:09,350 --> 00:07:12,978
How many times do I have to tell you?
It's Colonel!

114
00:07:14,730 --> 00:07:16,190
Nice setup.

115
00:07:16,482 --> 00:07:19,193
I want to know why
I did not get an upgrade.

116
00:07:19,318 --> 00:07:22,196
Because you are just a pilot!

117
00:07:23,238 --> 00:07:26,325
Now do your job
and pilot this ship!

118
00:07:27,660 --> 00:07:30,537
Just a pilot? We will see about that.

119
00:07:48,347 --> 00:07:50,224
All right, Cyclops, listen up!

120
00:07:50,265 --> 00:07:52,726
I want you to alert me
when we near the dreadnought.

121
00:07:52,851 --> 00:07:55,688
I have a plan
on how to attract their attention.

122
00:07:55,938 --> 00:07:58,732
<i>Relax. I already took care of it.</i>

123
00:08:02,736 --> 00:08:05,781
What do you mean? What did you do?

124
00:08:06,407 --> 00:08:10,077
I put us on a collision course
with the dreadnaught.

125
00:08:24,925 --> 00:08:27,136
See, Corporal? I am not just a pilot.

126
00:08:27,261 --> 00:08:30,264
You idiot! We're caught in a tractor beam!

127
00:08:51,076 --> 00:08:52,286
Hold it right there!

128
00:08:52,494 --> 00:08:54,455
Out of the way, tin cans!

129
00:08:57,291 --> 00:08:59,084
Let's check the cockpit.

130
00:09:04,965 --> 00:09:07,968
No sign of life. Just these droids.

131
00:09:08,469 --> 00:09:12,097
Continue your search while I take
these droids in for interrogation.

132
00:09:22,316 --> 00:09:24,318
Everyone just stay calm.

133
00:09:27,988 --> 00:09:29,031
Oh, my gosh!

134
00:09:30,282 --> 00:09:32,159
You are Republic droids!

135
00:09:32,284 --> 00:09:35,037
That is right. And I am their leader!

136
00:09:37,164 --> 00:09:38,707
Yeah ! I got him!

137
00:09:41,335 --> 00:09:43,170
Well, thanks for the assist, Qutee.

138
00:09:59,228 --> 00:10:00,521
All right, listen up.

139
00:10:00,646 --> 00:10:03,524
The next phase of my plan
is to reach C deck.

140
00:10:05,067 --> 00:10:06,360
We'll take this path here.

141
00:10:06,860 --> 00:10:09,571
Since the mechs won't draw
much attention, we'll go in a convoy.

142
00:10:10,239 --> 00:10:12,074
Cyclops, you lead the way.

143
00:10:12,199 --> 00:10:15,577
If anyone asks, you're taking the droids
on a repair job.

144
00:10:15,702 --> 00:10:18,539
-Got it?
-Yes, sir, uh...

145
00:10:19,373 --> 00:10:21,250
-Captain !
-It's Colonel!

146
00:10:21,375 --> 00:10:25,379
I swear, Cyclops,
you are gonna drive me crazy.

147
00:10:30,384 --> 00:10:34,721
Now, I want Flat Top to locate
the comm vault power supply,

148
00:10:34,847 --> 00:10:39,560
then use his laser to cut the main line
and cause a temporary loss in power.

149
00:10:40,727 --> 00:10:42,729
You can do it, Ceefor!

150
00:10:56,702 --> 00:10:58,537
Oh. Do not forget to lock down your...

151
00:11:08,380 --> 00:11:12,551
Sir. There was a temporary power loss
on C deck.

152
00:11:12,718 --> 00:11:15,262
Has the power been re-established?

153
00:11:15,596 --> 00:11:19,224
Yes. It was only a temporary fluctuation.

154
00:11:20,642 --> 00:11:22,102
Curious.

155
00:11:24,479 --> 00:11:25,898
All right, listen up.

156
00:11:25,981 --> 00:11:30,110
Cutting the power put the comm vault
security system in manual override.

157
00:11:30,277 --> 00:11:33,447
But someone still has to distract
some super battle droids...

158
00:11:33,572 --> 00:11:36,116
Oh, please, please, please! Let me do it.

159
00:11:36,158 --> 00:11:37,576
<i>Come on! Come on! Come on! Come on!</i>

160
00:11:37,618 --> 00:11:40,120
<i>Let me do it! Please!</i>

161
00:11:40,245 --> 00:11:43,081
<i>-Come on! Come on!</i>
-All right.

162
00:11:43,123 --> 00:11:45,083
You will not regret this, Corporal!

163
00:11:45,125 --> 00:11:46,960
I am not a...

164
00:11:54,593 --> 00:11:55,636
Halt.

165
00:11:56,303 --> 00:12:00,140
I have been ordered by General Grievous
to test comm vault security,

166
00:12:00,182 --> 00:12:01,808
and I need your help.

167
00:12:02,142 --> 00:12:03,644
Now, follow me.

168
00:12:11,151 --> 00:12:15,113
Now, I will go inside the comm vault
and send out a power surge.

169
00:12:16,156 --> 00:12:17,866
I need you two to stay here.

170
00:12:22,496 --> 00:12:24,665
It will not be safe for you
while I am working.

171
00:12:24,831 --> 00:12:27,000
- Are we clear?
- Yes, but...

172
00:12:27,167 --> 00:12:30,837
Good ! That is what I like. No questions.

173
00:12:32,005 --> 00:12:33,131
Huh?

174
00:12:35,175 --> 00:12:37,844
Thank you, thank you,
thank you very much.

175
00:12:37,970 --> 00:12:40,639
Quiet!
We need to keep moving.

176
00:12:40,681 --> 00:12:43,517
Beezee, open the comm vault
security door.

177
00:12:44,351 --> 00:12:46,853
Make sure it is not booby-trapped.

178
00:12:56,989 --> 00:13:01,201
You blockhead !
Now we're going to lose manual override!

179
00:13:01,702 --> 00:13:04,705
You... You terminated Beezee.

180
00:13:05,205 --> 00:13:09,001
It's not my fault he fried his circuitry!

181
00:13:09,042 --> 00:13:12,879
I didn't tell that nitwit
to attack the access panel!

182
00:13:13,505 --> 00:13:15,882
So what do we do now, Corporal?

183
00:13:19,344 --> 00:13:22,055
Look, we can still salvage this mission.

184
00:13:22,222 --> 00:13:24,016
If one of you could just...

185
00:13:24,057 --> 00:13:26,101
You need to re-access that panel,

186
00:13:26,226 --> 00:13:29,438
and we have to open
that comm vault door fast

187
00:13:29,563 --> 00:13:33,233
and grab the encryption module
before we're caught red-handed!

188
00:13:35,068 --> 00:13:37,571
No, I will not do it myself.

189
00:13:37,696 --> 00:13:38,905
I'm an officer!

190
00:13:39,031 --> 00:13:44,244
I've got no experience
in this type of crisis maneuver.

191
00:13:44,786 --> 00:13:49,750
You fought in the Battle of Geonosis.
That did not prepare you for a crisis?

192
00:13:49,875 --> 00:13:54,087
Well, technically I didn't
fight in that battle.

193
00:13:54,212 --> 00:13:57,215
I'm a military analyst by trade, and...

194
00:13:57,257 --> 00:13:59,092
You are a map reader?

195
00:14:01,595 --> 00:14:05,098
I am an accomplished battlefield strategist!

196
00:14:05,140 --> 00:14:09,269
I analyze the enemy terrain
and plot a course to victory.

197
00:14:09,311 --> 00:14:11,271
In other words, you read maps.

198
00:14:12,439 --> 00:14:14,274
You're off base here, Cyclops!

199
00:14:14,399 --> 00:14:17,069
I was chosen for my fearsome cunning,

200
00:14:17,611 --> 00:14:22,115
although my size
may have played a small factor.

201
00:14:24,076 --> 00:14:27,746
But do not think for a moment
that Colonel Meebur Gascon

202
00:14:27,829 --> 00:14:31,124
is going to relinquish command
of this mission.

203
00:14:31,583 --> 00:14:34,586
I have waited a lifetime
for this opportunity,

204
00:14:34,628 --> 00:14:40,300
and some ragtag collection of droids
is not going to deny me my destiny!

205
00:14:40,467 --> 00:14:44,805
So, one way or another,
I will open that comm vault door!

206
00:14:47,432 --> 00:14:50,519
Oh, there. Just like I planned it.

207
00:14:53,855 --> 00:14:56,316
Now, we're going to infiltrate this vault,

208
00:14:56,358 --> 00:15:00,362
neutralize the swarm mines,
and then secure the encryption module.

209
00:15:00,987 --> 00:15:02,197
Any questions?

210
00:15:02,322 --> 00:15:04,825
Have you ever been in a battle before?

211
00:15:06,827 --> 00:15:10,664
No, I have not.
But if you'd care to see what I'm made of,

212
00:15:10,705 --> 00:15:13,333
we can go to war right now, you and me,

213
00:15:13,375 --> 00:15:16,837
and probably get ourselves captured
by a Separatist.

214
00:15:16,962 --> 00:15:19,506
Or, we can execute my plan

215
00:15:19,631 --> 00:15:22,551
and come out of this mission
looking like heroes.

216
00:15:22,676 --> 00:15:25,178
The choice is yours, Cyclops.

217
00:15:29,391 --> 00:15:32,185
First of all, my name is WAC.

218
00:15:32,853 --> 00:15:35,730
Second of all, we will execute your plan.

219
00:15:36,022 --> 00:15:39,025
But you have to stop
calling us stupid names,

220
00:15:39,151 --> 00:15:40,861
Shorty.

221
00:15:43,071 --> 00:15:45,407
Very well, WAC.

222
00:15:47,200 --> 00:15:48,869
I'll play nice.

223
00:15:48,994 --> 00:15:52,539
But only until one of you screws up again!

224
00:16:02,174 --> 00:16:05,719
Sir, there has been another disturbance
on C deck.

225
00:16:06,178 --> 00:16:10,557
I will investigate this situation personally.

226
00:16:20,233 --> 00:16:22,736
All right, Pinky... I mean Qutee,

227
00:16:23,069 --> 00:16:25,030
this is your chance to shine.

228
00:16:25,071 --> 00:16:28,742
Use your magnet
to attract those swarm mines.

229
00:17:03,944 --> 00:17:06,988
There it is.
The encryption module.

230
00:17:09,616 --> 00:17:11,952
It's all up to you now, Artoo.

231
00:17:16,331 --> 00:17:17,624
Not so fast.

232
00:17:19,167 --> 00:17:20,418
Arms up!

233
00:17:26,466 --> 00:17:27,968
Gravity...

234
00:17:28,927 --> 00:17:30,971
Right! Turn it off! Quick!

235
00:18:26,359 --> 00:18:27,527
I will help you, Corporal!

236
00:18:34,576 --> 00:18:36,244
I'm gonna be sick.

237
00:18:36,870 --> 00:18:39,247
-Corporal? Are you okay?
-Look out!

238
00:18:52,260 --> 00:18:54,054
I will turn the gravity back on!

239
00:18:56,723 --> 00:18:58,099
Hurry, WAC, hurry!

240
00:19:18,703 --> 00:19:20,455
I'll take that.

241
00:19:20,580 --> 00:19:22,123
Good work, Artoo!

242
00:19:22,916 --> 00:19:25,585
<i>intruder alert. Intruder alert.</i>

243
00:19:25,627 --> 00:19:28,129
<i>Intruder alert. Intruder alert.</i>

244
00:19:28,463 --> 00:19:30,590
Let's move it out, D Squad!

245
00:19:40,934 --> 00:19:42,977
What are you doing?
We're going to get caught!

246
00:19:44,396 --> 00:19:47,107
Artoo says we cannot leave Beezee behind.

247
00:19:49,943 --> 00:19:53,113
Artoo's right.
We can repair him on the shuttle.

248
00:19:55,407 --> 00:19:57,617
There's trouble on C deck.

249
00:19:57,659 --> 00:19:59,452
Report there immediately.

250
00:20:10,296 --> 00:20:13,174
Get out of the way, you stupid astromechs!

251
00:20:20,974 --> 00:20:22,809
Funny thing about droids,

252
00:20:22,851 --> 00:20:25,311
last thing they'd expect to betray them,

253
00:20:25,353 --> 00:20:26,771
another droid.

254
00:20:30,775 --> 00:20:32,861
D Squad ! Let's go home.

255
00:21:05,894 --> 00:21:09,564
Ah ! My first mission, a rousing success.

256
00:21:09,731 --> 00:21:13,151
And a brilliant plan, if I do say so myself.

257
00:21:16,070 --> 00:21:20,533
I agree, Artoo.
The team's execution was not too shabby.

258
00:21:21,910 --> 00:21:26,706
Who knows, you droids
might just make decent soldiers after all.

259
00:21:29,083 --> 00:21:31,669
Oh, and you, too, WAC.

260
00:21:32,003 --> 00:21:33,046
Yes, sir,

261
00:21:33,171 --> 00:21:34,756
Colonel.

262
00:21:34,780 --> 00:21:39,780
http://hiqve.com/

